cancer and infection my aunt was diagnosed with cervical cancer about a year ago and had a historectomy sp the cancer went into remission but again about months ago it came back and spread recently her stomach filled up with fluid and she had to get it pumped out now she has an infection tell me honestly what does all of this mean her chances of survival i only want the brutal truth since it seems like nobody will tell us thank you i am sorry to hear that you aunt has had a recurrance of the cancer on chances of survival there are so many things that contribute to that where has the cancer spread is it operable are there good treatments chemo or raditation for the areas it has spread to the brutal truth is that not even the dr's know they can estimate but those vary widely i know a woman who wa diagnosed with stage iv ovarian cancer one of the cancers and levels that is concidered by many to be a 'death sentence' she had fluid drained many times she had surgeries and chemotherapy there were times that things were grim and touch and go as to whether she would survive or not that was nearly years ago and she is in remission and her prognosis is very good i also know another woman who had breast cancer it was caught early all thought he chances were very good she died of cancer less than a year later in spite of treatments and expectations having some estimate of life expectancy doesn't help it doesn't lessen the shock of the loss it doesn't lessen the grieving it only distracts you from her life dont' anticipate the end because whether we have day or years left worrying about the end only uses up what could be well spent and happy times focus on life for every day she has whether that is day or year or years good luck and god bless Cancer Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Ovarian cancer Stomach cancer Prostate cancer Lung cancer Breast cancer Endometrial cancer Cervical cancer Testicular cancer Colorectal cancer Malignant melanoma EastEnders Penile cancer Breastfeeding Esophagea